      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 6 and take your<strong> chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Rinse your <strong>brown rice</strong>, then add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return it to the pot</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1654602532584-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1654602532584-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1654602532584-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1654602532584-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1654602532584-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut them into strips</p><p>Peel and roughly chop your <strong>red onion[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>pepper strips</strong> and<strong> onion wedges</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 15 min or until the vegetables are tender – these are your <strong>roasted vegetables</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1654602545031-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1654602545031-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1654602545031-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1654602545031-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1654602545031-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While everything is cooking, combine your<strong> ground cumin</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> on a plate – this is your <strong>fajita</strong> <strong>seasoning</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>chicken breast strips</strong> into smaller strips</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken strips</strong> to the <strong>fajita seasoning</strong> and give everything a good mix up until it's fully coated in all the spices – this is your <strong>coated chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1690536092939-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1690536092939-x400.jpg",
